From 6e0f1f81f0bd0115459be22188e398d695bab5f5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 24 Jul 2025 12:29:07 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] UPSTREAM:CP|DP:wifi: ath12k: Skip stopping hw_queues in
 case of Mode-0 recovery.

As per upstream design In case of Mode-0 recovery the hw_quques
are stopped after that an mgmt frame coming in tx path is being
added into per CPU pending queue.

Now at the end of recovery when ath12k does hw_wake_queues() it
will check the pending queue and queue that frame immediatley
because of which after recovery disassoc frame is going to FW
before STA associates which leads to a FW crash.

Ideally when Mode-0 recovery is going on all mgm tx frames
should be freed as part of drv_tx instead of retaining in
pending queue and queue it later after Recovery.

To achieve that skip the ieee80211_stop_queues() in case of
Mode-0 recovery and queue all frames to drv_tx().

Now inside ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx() when recovery is in
progress these frames will be dropped.

Signed-off-by: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c     | 3 ++-
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c | 5 +++++
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
@@ -3593,7 +3593,8 @@ static void ath12k_core_reset(struct wor
 	mutex_lock(&ag->mutex);
 	ab->is_reset = true;
 
-	ath12k_core_mlo_hw_queues_stop(ab->ag);
+	if (ag->recovery_mode != ATH12K_MLO_RECOVERY_MODE0)
+		ath12k_core_mlo_hw_queues_stop(ab->ag);
 
 	for (i = 0; i < ag->num_devices; i++) {
 		partner_ab = ag->ab[i];
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
@@ -1448,6 +1448,11 @@ static void ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx(struc
 	ar = arvif->ar;
 	skb_cb->link_id = link_id;
 
+	if (unlikely(test_bit(ATH12K_FLAG_RECOVERY, &ar->ab->dev_flags))) {
+		ieee80211_free_txskb(hw, skb);
+		return;
+	}
+
 	if (sta) {
 		ahsta = ath12k_sta_to_ahsta(sta);
 		qos_tag = u32_get_bits(skb->mark, QOS_TAG_MASK);
